headline: Tyson Foods says supply-chain chief leaves after violating conduct rules
summary: CHICAGO (Reuters) -Tyson Foods' chief supply chain officer, who has also overseen its beef, pork and prepared foods businesses, left the U.S. meatpacker after violating the company's code of conduct, according to a statement.  The departure of Brady Stewart is the latest management change at Tyson Foods, which replaced former Chief Financial Officer John R. Tyson last year following arrests related to drinking.  Stewart could not immediately be reached for comment on Wednesday.
